==English==
===Adverb===
'''asunder'''
# into separate parts or pieces; [[apart]]
#:*''Lest anyone find her treasure, she tore the map '''asunder''' and cast its pieces into the wind.''
[[Category: English adverbs]]

===Etymology===

Swedish language has the word ''sönder'' for broken. This may or may not be related one or the other way.

